<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 4:54PM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Clare County through
600 PM EDT...
At 453 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Farwell, or 6 miles northwest of Clare, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Harrison around 510 PM EDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
